text.tspan: What does a yellow curb on the road mean?

tspan.tspan: A yellow curb on the road means that no person
shall stop, park or leave standing any motor vehicle
attended or unattended, except where necessary to
avoid conflict with other traffic or in compliance with
the direction of a peace officer.

The text "parking prohibited at yellow curb" and the section
name "18.01" suggest that parking is not allowed at a yellow
curb, except where a municipal bylaw provides otherwise.
This is because a curb painted yellow instructs every driver
of a vehicle that no person shall stop, park or leave
standing any motor vehicle attended or unattended, except
where necessary to avoid conflict with other traffic or in
compliance with the direction of a peace officer.
